{{Infobox video game |title = Autobahn Police Simulator |image = Autobahn Police Simulator cd cover.jpg |image_size = 200px |caption = Official DVD-ROM cover art. |genre = [[Simulation]], [[Casual game|Casual]], [[open-world]] |release = 26 August 2015 |platforms = [[Microsoft Windows]], [[iOS]] |publisher = Aerosoft GmbH |developer = Z-Software }}
'''''Autobahn Police Simulator''''' (Autobahn Polizei Simulator in German) is a police driving simulation game developed by Z-Software and published by Aerosoft GmbH.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.computerbild.de/artikel/cbs-Tests-PC-Autobahn-Polizei-Simulator-2015-12752045.html |title=Autobahn-Polizei Simulator 2015 im Test: Von wegen Alarm für Cobra 11 |last=Bleich |first=Olaf |website=computerbild.de}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.mobiflip.de/autobahnpolizei-simulator-fuer-ios-ist-da/ |title=Autobahnpolizei-Simulator für iOS ist da |last=Hesse |first=René |website=mobiflip.de}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.nat-games.de/2016/03/11/der-autobahnpolizei-simulator-patrouillenfahrt-jetzt-auch-mobil-erhaeltlich/ |title=Der Autobahnpolizei-Simulator – Patrouillenfahrt jetzt auch mobil erhältlich |last=Liesenhoff |first=Tobias |website=nat-games.de}}</ref> The sequel version of the game was released on December 7, 2017.
The game sets on [[Germany]]'s highway named [[Autobahn]] (Approximately 40&nbsp;km (25 miles) on the game). The game supports a gaming wheel for it to be more enjoyable and a third-person view or to first-person view. There are 40 missions in the game and free play mode is available. Players can also explore the world in foot and can manually open the vehicle's door. There are male and female characters on the game. There is also realistic radio communications and day and night cycle on the game.
On its gameplay, players will be able to use the "follow me" sign to flag down suspicious cars. Players can secure accidents, inspect truck loads, verifying TÜV (MOT) inspection stickers, and checking for alcohol or drugs.
