==Outside competition== As someone who has suffered from [[scoliosis]], Lee is a strong supporter of those affected by the disease, and now serves as the national spokesperson for the ''Scoliosis Association''.<ref>{{cite news |first=John |last=Morgan |newspaper=USA Today |url=https://www.usatoday.com/news/health/spotlighthealth/2003-04-18-jeanette-lee_x.htm |title=Jeanette Lee Shoots Down Scoliosis |location=McLean, VA, US |publisher=Gannett |at="Spotlight Health" section |accessdate=2012-02-24 |date=April 18, 2003}}</ref> Lee appeared on [[Fox Sports Net]]'s ''[[Sport Science (TV series)|Sport Science]]'', where she {{Cuegloss|Pocket|pocketed}} 12 balls in one [[trick shot]], on March 30, 2008.<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vgHadvGIxm4</ref> [[Orange County Choppers]] built the Black Widow Bike in Lee's honor on the TV show ''[[American Chopper]]''.<ref>[http://www.tv.com/american-chopper/the-jeanette-lee-black-widow-bike/episode/1311661/summary.html Reference to the Black Widow Bike]</ref>
==Personal life== Jeanette Lee lives in [[Tampa, Florida]] with her husband (professional pool player [[George Breedlove]]) and their children: stepdaughters Morgan Michelle Breedlove and Olivia Sue Breedlove, foster-son John Kang, daughters Cheyenne Lee Breedlove, Chloe Angelee Breedlove, Savannah Lee Breedlove.
