{{Nihongo|'''Nagoya Civic Assembly Hall'''|名古屋市公会堂|Nagoya-shi Kōkaidō}} is a concert hall located in [[Shōwa-ku, Nagoya]], Japan.

It was constructed in commemoration of the marriage of [[Hirohito|Emperor Hirohito]] and was opened on October 10, 1930.<ref>[http://www.nagoyashi-kokaido.jp/culture.html 自主文化事業案内｜名古屋市公会堂] Nagoya Civic Assembly Hall official website {{Ja icon}}</ref> It is often used as a boxing venue.<ref>[http://boxrec.com/location.php?country_code=JP&region_name=23&towncity_name=&towncity_id=10071&venue_name=&venue_id=15898&yyyy=&submit=Go BoxRec Boxing Records – Nagoya Civic Assembly Hall] [[BoxRec]]</ref>

